        "discriminators": [
          "The impulsive member of AIR. A pressure release is a single sharp broadband transient with a fast decay: envelope_attack_seconds of a few milliseconds and crest_factor ~9 or more, against ~4 for the steady AIR-BLOW and ~3.5 for AIR-HISS.",
          "Duration is the blunt instrument, and it is decisive: gated below 4 s and expected under half a second. AIR-HISS is gated to at least 0.5 s and typically runs tens of seconds — a 0.2 s event cannot be a slow leak.",
          "Front-loaded envelope (envelope_temporal_centroid ~0.25, envelope_skewness ~+2.0) is the exact inverse of AIR-SUCTION's inward swell."
        ],
